# Databases — committed deliberately. They ARE the artifact.
# Rebuilding from scratch is documented in §Reproducing Every Claim
# (eleven *_to_sqlite.fsx scripts), but the .db file is the data
# that the §For Journalists 10-minute verification protocol points
# at. Shipping it in git eliminates the Zenodo round-trip and the
# subscription-gated alternative both. See commit message for the
# Fuls-asymmetry argument that motivates the choice.

# LaTeX build artifacts
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.xmpdata
*.synctex*
pdfa.xmpi

# Alloy output dir
indus_corpus/

# CMake build dir (root-level only, not spec/build/)
/build/

# macOS
.DS_Store

# PDF — generated from tex, not tracked
# (ship the tex, not the pdf — Overleaf or cmake --build build --target paper)
*.pdf

# SQLite WAL/SHM files
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Distribution zips — build artifacts
*.zip

# Large archives — backed up to GDrive, not tracked in git
data/indus-valley-archive.tar.gz

# Source papers — third-party content, not tracked in git
# Ambedkar 1936 Annihilation of Caste is PD in India (life+60, 2017)
# but US URAA / EU life+70 are gray areas. Local-only; re-fetchable
# from the URLs noted in matching memory.db article rows.
data/source-papers/Ambedkar*
